comments.body:
Next meeting is April 16th! 
@kyhu65867 I would love to present the case for open source collaboration for OSCAL usage to achieve our automation outcomes. I have a presentation that discusses the strategy to build out OSCAL automation not to create an SSP in JSON, but rather to use automation to express compliance from automated control testing, one that is interoperable across frameworks and organizations due to adoption of a common data model and method for exchange through common APIs. We want to build conformance expression, not machine readable versions of point-in-time artifacts. 
I have a deck that I work from that I can share, and the project we are working under is OSCAL Compass as part of CNCF. Let me know!
